comments: Butler (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position and marginal contact occurs when VanVleet (TOR) engages and disengages with Butler on the perimeter.
Anunoby (MIA) reaches for the ball and avoids contact with Siakam's (TOR) arm during his steal attempt.
Adebayo (MIA) touches the ball, which has a chance to score, above rim level after it has hit the backboard.
Adebayo (MIA) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Siakam (TOR).
After the pick, Strus (MIA) and Siakam (TOR) engage and disengage, and the contact is marginal.
Butler (MIA) moves laterally and into VanVleet's (TOR) body, which affects his SQBR on the perimeter.
Tucker (MIA) does not deliver contact as he briefly places a resting hand on Anunoby's (TOR) body when he receives the pass.
Anunoby (TOR) lifts his pivot foot as he falls to the ground.
Trent Jr. (TOR) makes contact with the ball to deflect the inbounds pass. Any follow-through contact to Vincent's (MIA) arm after the deflection is deemed incidental.
Anunoby (TOR) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Anunoby (TOR) absorbs the contact from Butler (MIA) by collapsing his forearm in and then makes clean ball contact to block the driving shot attempt.

Butler (MIA) does not get ball height and makes contact with Barnes' (TOR) arm, which affects his put-back shot near the rim. The play was reviewed to make sure it occurred prior to the expiration of the game clock. After review, there were 2.9 seconds put back on the game clock.
Vincent (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in Anunoby's (TOR) path and absorbs the contact during the screen.
During the drive, Anunoby (TOR) has a resting forearm to Butler's (MIA) side and marginal contact occurs as the game clock expires prior to the shot attempt.
Tucker (MIA) momentarily rests his hand on VanVleet's (TOR) body and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in VanVleet's (TOR) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
VanVleet (TOR) extends his arms and delivers contact to Adebayo's (MIA) back, which affects his ability to pursue the rebound.
Anunoby (TOR) grabs Butler (MIA) and delivers contact that dislodges him as Anunoby attempts to squeeze through the screen.
Herro (MIA) takes more than 5 seconds to release his inbounds pass.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in Anunoby's (TOR) path and absorbs the contact during the screen.
Barnes (TOR) is in the paint and actively guarding an opponent within three seconds.
VanVleet (TOR) legally contests Vincent's (MIA) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
The 24-second shot clock expires before Barnes (TOR) releases his shot attempt.
Tucker (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in Anunoby's (TOR) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
Barnes (TOR) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Anunoby (TOR) legally contests Herro's (MIA) jump shot attempt. Herro loses his balance after returning to the ground and starting to backpedal.
Tucker (MIA) briefly rests a hand on Barnes' (TOR) side and marginal contact occurs as he immediately slides his hand off.
Adebayo (MIA) extends his arm out and makes contact with Trent Jr.'s (TOR) body and arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Anunoby (TOR) inadvertently steps on Tucker's (MIA) foot as he engages on the pick and incidental foot-to-foot contact occurs, which causes Tucker to lose his balance.
Anunoby (TOR) makes clean ball contact to dislodge it from Butler (MIA) and the ball remains inbounds before the Raptors recover it and call timeout.
Anunoby (TOR) has a resting forearm, which extends slightly into Tucker (MIA) as he deflects the inbound pass.
Butler (MIA) and Anunoby (TOR) pursue the loose ball and incidental contact occurs as they come together.
Butler (MIA) legally contests Anunoby's (TOR) jump shot attempt.
Anunoby (TOR) and Butler (MIA) mutually engage and disengage off-ball on the perimeter, and the contact is marginal.
Anunoby (TOR) is established in VIncent's (MIA) path and Vincent loses control of his dribble before any incidental foot to foot contact.
Siakam (TOR) dives to the floor and remains inbounds as he saves the ball from going out of bounds.

Tucker (MIA) reaches in and makes contact with VanVleet's (TOR) arm, which affects his ability to make his intended pass. The play was reviewed to see if it met the criteria for a clear path foul and after review a common foul was assessed.
Anunoby (TOR) gathers the ball on his left foot, establishing his right foot as his pivot, which he maintains.
Tucker (MIA) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact as Anunoby's (TOR) arm extends slightly at the end of the drive.
Adebayo (MIA) makes clean ball contact to tap the rebound away from Siakam (TOR).

Vincent (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in Anunoby's (TOR) path and absorbs the contact during the screen. Any contact with Vincent's face is deemed incidental as he crouches down before Anunoby engages. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
VanVleet (TOR) and Adebayo (MIA) mutually engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Herro (MIA) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the marginal contact from Siakam (TOR) during the drive.
Tucker (MIA) fails to fully clear the lane and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in Anunoby's (TOR) path and absorbs the contact during the screen.
Trent Jr. (TOR) delivers contact to Tucker (MIA), who is established in a screening position in his path, and dislodges him to the ground.
Herro (MIA) comes to a sudden stop and marginal contact occurs with Trent Jr. (TOR), which does not affect his SQBR on the perimeter.
Barnes (TOR) and Adebayo (MIA) mutually engage and disengage off-ball, and the contact is marginal.
Trent Jr. (TOR) retracts his resting forearm as Herro (MIA) gathers and enters his shooting motion, causing marginal contact to occur.
Herro (MIA) briefly places two hands to Siakam's (TOR) body and marginal contact occurs, which does not affect Siakam's ability to make his intended pass.
Adebayo (MIA) avoids making contact with Anunoby's (TOR) arm during his put-back shot attempt.
Adebayo (MIA) cleanly taps the ball away from Anunoby (TOR) during the rebound.
A timeout is called by the Heat bench with 1.7 seconds left on the game clock.
During the inbound, Barnes (TOR) and Adebayo (MIA) mutually engage and disengage, and the contact is marginal.
Tucker (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in Anunoby's (TOR) path and absorbs the contact during the screen.
Barnes (TOR) maintains a legal guarding position during the play at the basket by Herro (MIA).
VanVleet (TOR) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Siakam (TOR) fumbles the ball upon receiving the pass and is allowed to regain control and start his dribble.
Vincent (MIA) legally contests Trent Jr.'s (TOR) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
VanVleet (TOR) legally contests Herro's (MIA) jump shot attempt.
Trent Jr. (TOR) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs with Vincent's (MIA) arm during his attempt to tie the ball up.
Siakam (TOR) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the offensive loses control of the ball.
Barnes (TOR) briefly places a hand on Adebayo's (MIA) waist and marginal contact occurs, which does not affect his ability to get to the inbounds pass.
Trent Jr.'s (TOR) body touches the baseline out of bounds while he is in contact with the ball on his tie up attempt.
Anunoby (TOR) makes contact with Adebayo's (MIA) right wrist, which affects his ability to maintain control of the ball.
Anunoby (TOR) secures the loose ball before the 24 second shot clock expires for the Heat.
Adebayo (MIA) makes clean ball contact as he goes to the ground to try and steal the ball back from Anunoby (TOR).
Vincent (MIA) makes clean hand-on-ball contact as Siakam (TOR) passes.
Tucker (MIA) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.

VanVleet (TOR) loses his balance before Adebayo (MIA) makes clean hand-on-ball contact to dislodge it at the end of the drive. Any follow-through contact with Adebayo or Butler (MIA) after the dislodge is deemed incidental.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in Anunoby's (TOR) path and absorbs the contact during the pick.
Tucker (MIA) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.

Replay review of the foul called on Siakam (TOR) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Herro (MIA) briefly places a hand to Siakam's front, and the contact is marginal as it does not affect his SQBR. Siakam overtly and abnormally hooks Herro's arm, which affects his ability to defend during the drive.
Adebayo (MIA) establishes himself in a screening position in Trent Jr.'s (TOR) path and absorbs the contact during the screen.
Barnes (TOR) legally contests Herro's (MIA) jump shot attempt.
Tucker (MIA) makes clean ball contact as he tries to steal the ball from Anunoby (MIA).
Adebayo (MIA) commits a take foul on Siakam (TOR).
Barnes (TOR) and Adebayo (MIA) mutually engage and disengage, and marginal contact occurs during the inbounds.
Vincent's (MIA) right foot steps on the sideline after receiving the pass.
